    <div class="container mt-4 my-5">
        <div class="fs-1 my-3" style="text-align: center;font-family: 'Abril Fatface', cursive;">Our Story</div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="fs-4 text-justify px-3 mt-0" style="font-family: 'Baloo Bhai 2', cursive;"> <br>WiTech (Women in Technology) is a registered non-profit
                organization that was founded in the Philippines by Audrey P in 2016. WiTech aims to educate,
                inspire and empower women and youth to break gender barriers, pursue careers in tech, and use their
                abilities to make a difference in society. <br>

                After discovering a huge gender gap in the tech industry, Audrey started a blog wherein she posted
                articles featuring women in tech she interviewed to promote their stories and celebrate their journeys
                in the male - dominated fields.
                <br>
                In 2017, WiTech rebranded into a community organization that now has hundreds of people in the 7
                branches across the world - and counting!
            </div>
            <br>
        </div>
